The generic surface is rotated N-times which create N slices
or levels. The triangles become pentahedra and the quadrangles
become hexahedra.


ATTENTION: NO VERTEX of the surface must be on the rotation axis
because a such vertex transform a triangle into a pyramid which
is NOT a Mefisto finite element!

The total rotation angle can reach 360 degrees.

Example: 
V15.1; I; 15; INITIAL_SURFACE; P1_AXE; P2_AXE; 4; {rotations}
1; {angles for each rotation}
20; 30; 40; 50; {degrees}
{The rotations add from the initial surface}

Define a volume by 4 rotations of 20, 50, 90 and 140 degrees
of the initial surface around the axis P1_AXE  P2_AXE
